trend_summary: Forest gives way to more cropland at the northern tongue and south-east, while a central quarry/industrial pad grows, peaks, then starts revegetating. Built structures add slowly along the main road, but the airstrip stays constant. Net result is slightly higher human footprint yet still a sparsely settled rural landscape.
notable_changes: Central light-tan quarry/industrial platform enlarges through mid-series, then shows partial closure and vegetation return in the latest view.
Agricultural fields expand northward and south-east, fragmenting contiguous forest cover.
